title: Sidewall, 1850
provenance: From "Ellarslie", the home of Henry McCall, Trenton, New Jersey. Built by John Notman, c. 1850. Used in stair hall.
description: Stylized leaf and flower on shades of beige and gray, probably originally metallic.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1850.
1850. 58 x 46 cm (22 13/16 x 18 1/8 in.). Gift of Mrs. Robert Grieff. 1976-20-1.
